<paragraph blockId="7.[189,303,1456,1482]" box="[189,303,1456,1482]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1456,1482]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1456,1482]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1503,1673]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[189,313,1503,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis box="[189,313,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles the species of the ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burla" authorityYear="1954" box="[681,828,1503,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikananu">
<emphasis box="[681,828,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. nikananu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T." box="[1052,1399,1503,1530]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="427 - 432" part="96" refId="ref13191" refString="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T. 1992. L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 96: 427 - 432." title="L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1992">
Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05968" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="1992.0">1992 in</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
males having completely yellow abdominal tergites. However, it differs from the species of the ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burla" authorityYear="1954" box="[199,343,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikananu">
<emphasis box="[199,343,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. nikananu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ in males having sex combs on the two first tarsomeres of the foreleg (the comb is lost or reduced on the second tarsomere in the ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burla" authorityYear="1954" box="[861,1007,1611,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikananu">
<emphasis box="[861,1007,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. nikananu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’) and lacking a dorsal tooth-like protuberance on the surstylus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1713,2027]" lastBlockId="8.[189,1399,267,560]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<bibRefCitation author="Lachaise D." box="[189,381,1713,1739]" journalOrPublisher="University of Paris VI, France" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref12537" refString="Lachaise D. 1979. Speciation, Coevolution et Adaptation des Populations de Drosophilides en Afrique Tropicale. PhD Thesis, University of Paris VI, France." title="Speciation, Coevolution et Adaptation des Populations de Drosophilides en Afrique Tropicale" type="book" year="1979">Lachaise (1979)</bibRefCitation>
attributed a laboratory strain collected from Makoukou (
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1152,1713,1740]" name="Gabon" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Gabon</collectingCountry>
) to this species, and showed that it could produce fertile F 
<specimenCount box="[629,738,1749,1775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="female">1 females</specimenCount>
and sterile F 
<specimenCount box="[892,978,1749,1775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="male">1 males</specimenCount>
when its females were crossed with males of the strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[456,587,1785,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis box="[456,587,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[631,926,1785,1811]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael V." box="[939,1103,1785,1811]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="179 - 189" part="109" refId="ref12862" refString="Rafael V. 1984. Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France 109: 179 - 189." title="Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1984">Rafael (1984)</bibRefCitation>
attributed another strain from Kunden (
<collectingCountry box="[363,489,1821,1847]" name="Cameroon" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
) to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[536,658,1821,1847]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis box="[536,658,1821,1847]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and showed that it could not hybridize with the same strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[189,316,1857,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis box="[189,316,1857,1883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or with the strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bock &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1972" box="[551,666,1858,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsacasi">
<emphasis box="[551,666,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. tsacasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[702,984,1857,1883]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. Intriguingly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael V." box="[1145,1304,1857,1883]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="179 - 189" part="109" refId="ref12862" refString="Rafael V. 1984. Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France 109: 179 - 189." title="Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1984">Rafael (1984)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that both the Gabonese and Cameroonian strains of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[864,987,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis box="[864,987,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed some differences in body size and pigmentation from the 
<typeStatus box="[570,621,1929,1955]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
material from 
<collectingCountry box="[800,944,1929,1955]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
. She also found that the Cameroonian strain hybridized readily with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="1982" box="[541,716,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassya">
<emphasis box="[541,716,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. malagassya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though both F1 sexes were sterile. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kopp A." box="[1137,1287,1965,1992]" journalOrPublisher="Drosophila Information Service" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="33 - 35" part="99" refId="ref12419" refString="Kopp A. 2016. Strong reproductive isolation among African species of the Drosophila montium subgroup. Drosophila Information Service 99: 33 - 35." title="Strong reproductive isolation among African species of the Drosophila montium subgroup" type="journal article" year="2016">Kopp (2016)</bibRefCitation>
analyzed a strain collected from the island of 
<collectingCountry box="[628,747,2001,2027]" name="Sao Tome and Principe" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">São Tomé</collectingCountry>
and attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[963,1086,2001,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis box="[963,1086,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by J.R. David, and found that it produced sterile F 
<specimenCount box="[481,567,267,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="male">1 males</specimenCount>
and females when crossed with the same strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bock &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1972" box="[1166,1283,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsacasi">
<emphasis box="[1166,1283,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. tsacasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Da Lage J. - L. &amp; Kergoat G. J. &amp; Maczkowiak F. &amp; Silvain J. - F. &amp; Cariou M. - L. &amp; Lachaise D." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="47 - 63" part="45" refId="ref12250" refString="Da Lage J. - L., Kergoat G. J., Maczkowiak F., Silvain J. - F., Cariou M. - L. &amp; Lachaise D. 2007. A phylogeny of Drosophilidae using the Amyrel gene: questioning the Drosophila melanogaster species group boundaries. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research 45: 47 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0469.2006.00389. x" title="A phylogeny of Drosophilidae using the Amyrel gene: questioning the Drosophila melanogaster species group boundaries" type="journal article" year="2007">
Da Lage 
<emphasis box="[189,248,305,331]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
analyzed the sequence of the nuclear gene 
<emphasis box="[848,932,305,331]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Amyrel</emphasis>
from a strain collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[1278,1348,305,331]" name="Benin" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Benin</collectingCountry>
and found it to be sister to the strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bock &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1972" box="[601,718,344,369]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsacasi">
<emphasis box="[601,718,344,369]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. tsacasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[758,1046,343,369]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Prigent S. R. &amp; Suwalski A. &amp; Veuille M." box="[1057,1293,343,369]" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 20" part="287" refId="ref12801" refString="Prigent S. R., Suwalski A. &amp; Veuille M. 2017. Connecting systematic and ecological studies using DNA barcoding in a population survey of Drosophilidae (Diptera) from Mt Oku (Cameroon). European Journal of Taxonomy 287: 1 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2017.287" title="Connecting systematic and ecological studies using DNA barcoding in a population survey of Drosophilidae (Diptera) from Mt Oku (Cameroon)" type="journal article" year="2017">
Prigent 
<emphasis box="[1149,1208,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
partially sequenced the mitochondrial gene 
<emphasis box="[609,660,382,408]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">COI</emphasis>
from two specimens from Mount Oku in 
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1297,381,407]" name="Cameroon" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and did not recover such affinity (
<figureCitation box="[504,579,419,445]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1713,1739]" captionTargetBox="[206,1387,908,1645]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1400,879,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Comparison of Bayesian phylogenies of the ‘D. seguyi species subgroup’ Yassin, 2018 inferred from mitochondrial COI (left) and nuclear Amyrel (right) genes. Nodes supported by&gt;95% posterior probability (pp) are labeled with black circles. An asterisk refers to species sequenced here, whereas two asterisks refer to the sequence of D. vulcana Graber, 1957 of Da Lage et al. (2007), which turned out to belong to D. seguyi Smart, 1945 from Kenya (see the text). Note the discrepancy in position of different geographical strains of D. bakoue Tsacas &amp; Lachaise, 1974 (in red) between the two genes. Species belonging to ‘D. bocqueti species complex’ Tsacas &amp; Lachaise, 1974, ‘D. bakoue species complex’ Rafael, 1984, ‘D. nikananu species complex’ Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard, 1992, and ‘D. megapyga species complex’ Lachaise &amp; Tsacas, 2001 are highlighted in orange, green, yellow and red, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251573/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). These results suggest that at least two different species may have been attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[407,530,457,483]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis box="[407,530,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which the strains from 
<collectingCountry box="[890,960,457,483]" name="Benin" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Benin</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1140,457,483]" name="Sao Tome and Principe" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">São Tomé</collectingCountry>
are closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bock &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1972" box="[189,305,496,521]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsacasi">
<emphasis box="[189,305,496,521]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. tsacasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the strains from 
<collectingCountry box="[612,690,495,521]" name="Gabon" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Gabon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[745,867,495,521]" name="Cameroon" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
are distant. The relation of these species with the true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[285,406,533,559]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis box="[285,406,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[477,615,533,560]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
needs more investigations.
</paragraph>
